bc62-2219557b7e55","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/aCjd3XJoUotcnBaULgd3QJ.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/57987-kindle-fire-hdx13.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/aCjd3XJoUotcnBaULgd3QJ.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"aCjd3XJoUotcnBaULgd3QJ","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/aCjd3XJoUotcnBaULgd3QJ.jpg","alt":""},"id":"a4a98884-a4fd-4945-9b9f-14b444f0f513","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["This Kindle has a nice lengthy battery life for a tablet and even beats out its Apple competitor, the iPad Mini, by one more hour of battery life during normal use. When you are using the Kindle Fire HDX for browsing the web, using apps, watching videos, jamming out to tunes and reading, you should expect to get about 11 hours out of it before you need to recharge it. However, if you are just reading, you may get up to 17 hours before needing to plug it in. Charging it from zero battery to 100 percent should take under six hours if you use the included micro-USB power adapter.","You will have 16GB of space to fill with books, movies, magazines, photos and much more, and you’ll also have Amazon’s free cloud storage to take advantage of. However, 32GB and 64GB Kindle Fire HDX options are also available for an additional cost. As with all other Kindle devices, you can use the Whispersync function to synchronize purchases and bookmarks across all of your Kindle devices."]},"id":"e7e0b1c7-d30c-4bd7-bb57-8f4793964308","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Help &amp; Support"},"id":"0011d117-6bee-4355-96a6-4019c88c06ce","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/zcqS4dPuonnGqfXEJxNACJ.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/57987-kindle-fire-hdx5.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/zcqS4dPuonnGqfXEJxNACJ.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"zcqS4dPuonnGqfXEJxNACJ",